BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Central Bank Releases Budget Surplus, Vale Call

-- B y   R o b i n   S t r i n g e r
-- 
2011-07-29T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/brazil-daybook-central-bank-releases-budget-surplus-vale-call.html
Brazil ’s budget surplus probably
grew to 14.5 billion reais in June, according to the median
estimate of 13 economists surveyed by Bloomberg. The central
bank releases the result at 10:30 a.m. in Brasilia.  GOVERNMENT:
*Finance Minister  Guido Mantega  attends the results of the PAC
program to accelerate growth program at 10 a.m.
*Central bank President Alexandre Tombini has meetings in
Brasilia.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Vale, the world’s biggest iron-ore producer, discusses its
second-quarter earnings with investors on a conference call at
12 p.m.  ECONOMY:
*Net public debt as a percentage of GDP at 10:30 a.m.
*Nominal budget balance at 10:30 a.m.
*Primary budget balance at 10:30 a.m.  EARNINGS:
*Souza Cruz (CRUZ3 BZ) after market.  EQUITIES:
*Vale (VALE3 BZ) reported second-quarter profit of $6.45
billion, up 74 percent.
*Embraer (EMBR3 BZ) boosted its 2011 forecast for net sales to
$5.8 billion from $5.6 billion. *Usiminas (USIM5 BZ) approved a
credit line of $750 million.  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 0.7 percent to 58,708.25.
*The real fell 0.8 percent to 1.5672 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
